text:
I ordered sliced fish with ginger and onion cooking style for takeaway, but when I opened it at home, I was shocked. It wasn't sliced fish at all. The fish pieces were heavily battered and deep-fried, then coated in a sauce, resembling more like a sweet and sour pork dish.
I ate few pieces and found that the fish inside was soft and mushy, clearly why they used the thick batter. For $12, this was a complete misrepresentation of the dish I ordered and definitely not worth the price. I won't be buying from them again.

When you ordered one of their horfun, yee mee or hokkien mee. You would realised the quality of their ingredients. The prawns given were big and fresh, pork is good and even the fish cake taste nicer than the standard dodo or lichuan that other zichar stall uses. From the selection of ingredients, we can tell that this zichar stall really put their heart into what they are cooking for their customers. üëçüëçüëç

I think this is the better zi char spot in the entire area of teck whye! Definitely coming back to try other dishes soon.

Ps! Just that the horfun probably need slight improvement, mine was water-ish and plain tasting :(
Small zi char stall with many variety of food. Cheap, simple and nice food.  Just that is in coffee shop, environment abit warm.

wide variety of food for a small zichar store, food is flavourful and just yums üòã portion is big for the amount paid ü§© super worth! all the uncles also very friendly but quite hard to get seats during peak hours as the coffee shop is small
